Package fr.inria.verveine.extractor.java

Class AbstractDictionary<B>

java.lang.Object
fr.inria.verveine.extractor.java.AbstractDictionary<B>
Type Parameters:
B - The class of the keys, typically a JDT binding or a CDT binding, ...
Direct Known Subclasses:
JavaDictionary
public class AbstractDictionary<B> extends Object
A dictionnary of Famix entities to help create them and find them back
Author:
anquetil Entities are mapped to keys. Typically the key will be a binding provided by the parser used

    • typeToImpVar

      @Deprecated protected Map<Type,AbstractDictionary<B>.ImplicitVars> typeToImpVar
      Deprecated.
      Yet another dictionary for implicit variables ('self' and 'super') Because they are implicit, they may not have a binding provided by the parser, or may have the same binding than their associated type so they can't be kept easily in keyToEntity

  • Method Details

    • recoverExistingRepository

      protected void recoverExistingRepository()
      Resets the dictionnary in a proper state after loading entities from an existing MSE file:
      • map all named entities to their names in mapName
      • reset some boolean properties (e.g. isStub) that are false (they are not saved in the mse file and therefore not initialized)

    • getEntityByKey

      public TNamedEntity getEntityByKey(B key)
      Returns the Famix Entity associated to the given key. Note: Be careful than ImplicitVariables share the same binding than their associated Class and cannot be retrieved with this method. In such a case, this method will always retrieve the Class associated to the key. To get an ImplicitVariable from the key, use getImplicitVariableByBinding(Object, String)
      Parameters:
      key - -- the key
      Returns:
      the Famix Entity associated to the binding or null if not found

    • createFamixEntity

      protected <T extends TNamedEntity & TSourceEntity> T createFamixEntity(Class<T> fmxClass, String name, boolean persistIt)
      Creates and returns a FAMIX Entity of the type fmxClass. The Entity is always created (see ensureFamixEntity(Class, Object, String, boolean)).
      Parameters:
      fmxClass - -- the FAMIX class of the instance to create
      name - -- the name of the new instance must not be null (and this is not tested)
      persistIt - -- whether the Entity should be persisted in the Famix repository
      Returns:
      the FAMIX Entity or null in case of a FAMIX error

    • ensureFamixEntity

      protected <T extends TNamedEntity & TSourceEntity> T ensureFamixEntity(Class<T> fmxClass, B bnd, String name, boolean persistIt)
      Returns a FAMIX Entity of the type fmxClass and maps it to its binding bnd (if not null). The Entity is created if it did not exist.
      Parameters:
      fmxClass - -- the FAMIX class of the instance to create
      bnd - -- the binding to map to the new instance
      name - -- the name of the new instance (used if bnd == null)
      persistIt - -- whether the Entity should be persisted in the Famix repository
      Returns:
      the FAMIX Entity or null if bnd was null or in case of a FAMIX error

    • ensureFamixMethod

      public Method ensureFamixMethod(B key, String name, String sig, TType ret, TWithMethods owner, boolean persistIt)
      Returns a FAMIX Method with the given name, creating it if it does not exist yet
      Parameters:
      key - to which the entity will be mapped (may be null, but then it will be difficult to recover the entity)
      name - -- the name of the FAMIX Method (MUST NOT be null, but this is not checked)
      sig - -- method's signature, including type of parameters and return type (should not be null, but it will work if it is)
      ret - -- Famix Type returned by the method (ideally should only be null in case of a constructor, but will accept it in any case)
      owner - -- type defining the method (should not be null, but it will work if it is)
      persistIt - -- whether the Method should be persisted in the Famix repository
      Returns:
      the FAMIX Method or null in case of a FAMIX error

      Returns:
